<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-07-14T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-07-14T15:00:00-05:00" n="509" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d509">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/306: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Child</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-14T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 14,
                                        1922—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>98. Your 110, July 12, 1 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Does the note of the Italian Government give formal approval to the
                            amended resolution quoted in the Department’s No. 80 of June 3, 1 p.m.,
                            as requested in the Department’s 94 of June 29, 3 p.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>